<p>Both VP external candidates were no-shows at the first debate of the 2014 AMS election campaign.</p>
<p>The position has two candidates this year — Bahareh Jokar, the current associate VP external, and Jon Snow (real name Philip He), who is running as a joke candidate — but neither was present at the start of Monday night&#8217;s debate at Brock Hall.</p>
<p>Both candidates arrived at Brock Hall past the designated time slot for their debate.</p>
<p>Jokar said she had confused the start time of tonight&#8217;s debates with tomorrow&#8217;s debate at Vanier residence.</p>
<p>&#8220;Unfortunately I accidentally saved tomorrow&#8217;s time into my phone,&#8221; said Jokar. &#8220;I was operating under the impression that these debates started at 5:15 versus five o&#8217;clock, so by the time I got there, my time slot had already passed.&#8221;</p>
<p>Jokar said she asked the elections committee if she could participate after the Board of Governors debate that was underway, but was told that she would have to wait until the very end of the evening&#8217;s debate schedule, which would have interfered with her commitments as a residence advisor in Ponderosa Commons.</p>
<p>&#8220;Unfortunately because of my little mishap it just didn&#8217;t work out for me to participate in the debate this evening,&#8221; said Jokar.</p>
<p>Snow also arrived late for the debate.</p>
<p>&#8220;Earlier today I was in the office section of the SUB, and it just so happened that&#8217;s when two infiltrators from SFU attacked. While I did manage to save all the execs from an assassination attempt, I burned my hand in the process. I was in the care of my maester for most of the day. My hand&#8217;s mostly okay now, but he told me I&#8217;m supposed to remain in observation,&#8221; said Snow. &#8220;But I snuck out &#8230; and here I am late for the debate.&#8221;</p>
<p>The VP external is responsible for lobbying on behalf of UBC students. The role involves advocating on issues such as tuition, transit and childcare. They will also oversee the transition from the U-Pass to the Compass Card.</p>
<p>The next debate involving the VP external candidates is scheduled for Jan. 27 at 4 p.m. at Hillel House. Both Jokar and Snow said they plan to attend.</p>
