<p>This weekend, the AMS elections committee posted that VP administration candidate Ava Nasiri had rejected several endorsements which she actually accepted.</p>
<p>The rejected endorsements went up Friday and were removed Sunday afternoon. </p>
<p>Elections administrator Roddy Lai said this was a result of a miscommunication. According to AMS policy, the elections committee must post candidates&#8217; acceptance or rejection of endorsements.</p>
<p>&#8220;She needed final confirmation from them and that&#8217;s why the miscommunication happened, because she informed us not to post these, and we thought she was rejecting them, which was not the case,&#8221; Lai said.</p>
<p>Lai was contacted by Nasiri and the posting was removed. He said once the AMS receives final confirmation, the endorsements will be reposted as accepted. </p>
<p>The post <a href="http://ubyssey.ca/news/ams-endorsements-confusion-239/">Accepted endorsements posted as rejected endorsements on AMS elections website</a> appeared first on <a href="http://ubyssey.ca">The Ubyssey</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"
    
    
    
    
    
    
