<p>AMS President Caroline Wong has dropped out of the race for Board of Governors representative.</p>
<p>Wong said she dropped out to pursue study abroad opportunities, a decision made easier by her confidence in the remaining candidates. </p>
<p>Initially worried about her eligibility for studying abroad after not taking a full course load during her time as president, Wong said she decided to run for BoG rep because, after serving as an AMS executive and now as president, she felt she would make a good student representative.</p>
<p>&#8220;I figured I might as well contribute with everything I&#8217;ve learned about the university,&#8221; Wong said.</p>
<p>However, after observing what she considered to be a strong field of candidates, Wong said she had no qualms about bowing out of the race. She said she is continuing to try and study abroad, ideally in Italy.</p>
<p>Wong declined to endorse any of the other BoG reps, saying the AMS executive team had made a collective decision not to endorse candidates.</p>
